      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Common Tiles, Common Opportunity</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The bag contains <span class="text-white font-medium">12 E tiles and 6 R tiles</span> — that's 18 tiles that can form ER. You'll have E+R on your rack frequently. ER isn't about scoring big (2pts is minimal). It's about <span class="text-white font-medium">rack management</span>: dumping common tiles to draw better ones, while setting up hooks and crosswords for your next turn.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy: When to Play ER</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Rack balance:</span> If your rack has 3+ vowels or duplicate common letters, playing ER dumps 2 tiles and draws 2 fresh ones. Better rack = better next turn.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Create crossword lanes:</span> Place ER where it opens premium squares for your next play. The letters E and R are among the most connectable — E forms 2-letter words with almost every consonant.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel play powerhouse:</span> E connects with: AE, BE, DE, FE, HE, ME, NE, OE, PE, RE, WE, YE. R connects with: AR, ER, OR. This means ER placed parallel can score bonus points from crosswords.</p>
        </div>
